<P>As it currently works(until DOM support is added), it is simply a =
function=20
that takes a string and parses it, extracting the tags and their =
attributes. It=20
collects the tags and all of the textual information into some objects, =
then=20
returns the object as one main "root" object.</P>
<P>For now, the API is extreemly simple and only for read-only purposes. =
There=20
are four types of objects, listed here with each of their properties:=20
<UL>
  <LI>An Element: &lt;tag&gt;=20
  <UL>
    <LI>type - "element"=20
    <LI>name - string containing the elements name=20
    <LI>attributes - array containing name=3Dvalue pairs for each =
attribute=20
    <LI>contents - array containing objects for everything within the =
tag=20
  </LI></UL>
  <LI>PI's - Processing Instructions: &lt;? some data ?&gt;=20
  <UL>
    <LI>type - "pi"=20
    <LI>value - string containing the data in the pi for the target =
</LI></UL>
  <LI>Comments: &lt;!-- my comment --&gt;=20
  <UL>
    <LI>type - "comment"=20
    <LI>value - string containing the text in the comment </LI></UL>
  <LI>Textual Information=20
  <UL>
    <LI>type - "chardata"=20
    <LI>value - string containing the text </LI></UL></LI></UL>
<P></P>
